#AD In winter, as temperatures drop and the demand for gas becomes higher, it’s important to understand what 4 factors impact your energy costs each month:

1) Usage – The primary factor that impacts your monthly energy bill is usage – the amount of energy used during a billing cycle – it’s cold outside, make sure you seal those windows and other cracks around your house/apartment. Swap out old lightbulbs for LEDs and turn lights off when you leave a room.
2) Weather – A couple days of extreme cold weather can make heating equipment run longer, increasing your energy use – I like to dress cozy so I can keep my heat low.
3) Days billed – Fewer days in the billing cycle typically results in a lower energy bill, compared to a billing cycle with more days
4) Household changes – More people in the house often means gas appliances are used more, or you may even make adjustments to the thermostat to make people more comfortable – I use a Star certified smart thermostat to keep things in check no matter how many people are over!

Many of these newcomers settled on the west side of the city; they were primarily from County Cork, and thus the neighborhood came to be known as Corktown. The Hamtramck Labor Day Festival is back with the 2023 Yacht Club Canoe Races! 🛶💨

An annual tradition of the @hamtramcklabordayfestival, the competition involves staff from local bars competing in decorated go-carts that look like canoes! 

Once the contest begins, it is pure unadulterated chao as the teams race toward the finish line and spectators on either side splash them with buckets of water, shoot them with squirt guns and pelt them with water balloons. 💧🔫🎈

The bar that wins is awarded a wooden captain’s wheel, which, much like the Stanley Cup, will be inscribed with the bar’s name. Congratulations to @whiskeyhamtramck for last year’s win, who will be crowned this year? 🏆👀

The races are part of the annual 43rd Hamtramck Labor Day Festival that runs until Monday! 🥳 Featuring live music (including an appearance by Detroit’s viral star @gmaccash), local vendors, carnival rides, wrestling, and much more. Admission is free! 🎪🥳

📍 Located less than 15 minutes from downtown Detroit, Hamtramck is often referred to as “The World in Two Square Miles” and holds the title of being the most diverse city in Michigan. Come with us to spend a festive day in Southwest Detroit! 📍🎄

From community landmarks to new must-see spots, join us and @colindetroit for a day exploring some of the best locations to check out and explore in Southwest this holiday season. 🍰🍹🇲🇽

Check out each of them below to learn more about the story behind their location! 👇

📍 Mexicantown Bakery @mexicantownbakery 
A community stable in Southwest Detroit for almost 30 years, if you haven’t been yet it needs to be on your Southwest bucketlist! They sell everything from buns, cookies, churros, conchas, bread and more among their famous tres leches cakes.

📍 Flamingo Vintage @flamingovintagedetroit 
Owned by Nikki Neuzil & Finn Formica, Flamingo Vintage is stylish and funky spot located in a 100-year-old renovated art deco store in the heart of Southwest Detroit!

📍 Blitzen’s on Bagley / Goblin Sushi @onbagley @goblindetroit 
On Bagley is a bar that has rotating festive pop-up experiences! Check out their full menu of holiday pop-up drinks and grab some delicious sushi from Goblin which is right next door

📍 Mutiny Bar @mutinybar 
Decked out in sparkling lights and a cozy fresh vibe, Mutiny Bar has been serving up delicious drinks in Southwest Detroit since 2017! They also have karaoke every Thursday

📍 El Parian 3 Taco Truck
🌮 One of Southwest Detroit’s tastiest food trucks, check out El Parian! They are known for their delicious tacos al pastor and birria
Address: 4802 Vernor Hwy (They also have 2 other locations in Southwest)
